Rishi Sadhir
Project 3 - pittar

* Introduction
  A command line utitlity used to compress a list files/directories. Additionally, files/directories may be appeneded to an existing executable. One may completely or selectively decompress files.

* Compilation
  This program was compiled using gcc version 4.2. Versions prior to 4.0 will find trouble with the -fnested-functions flag that is required to 
compile this program. If this is the case, the executables have been provided as well.

* Usage
  pittar {-c|-a|-x|-m|-p} <archive-file> <file/directory list>

  where
   - c = compress
   - a = append
   - x = extract
   - m = prints hierarchies
   - p = print metadata

* Problems
  None known.
